<FIRST>r i PM-China-Spies     02-15 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-China-Spies,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>China Says It Has Arrested Two Men Who Spied for Taiwan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities in the southwestern province of
Sichuan have arrested a miner and another man for spying for
Taiwan's military, an official report said today.
   The China News Service said Deng Dongsheng, the coal miner,
entered a spy ring run by Chen Sumei in late 1987.
   It said the two regularly reported ``secrets'' to Taiwanese
authorities, although it did not specify the nature of the
intelligence they provided.
   ``They also developed an underground organization,'' the report
said.
   Earlier this year, public security agents busted the ring ``and
seized a large amount of proof of the spy activitiy,'' the report
said. Both Chen and Deng have admitted they were spies, it said.
   Every few months, the state-run media reports that Taiwanese
spies have been arrested.
   China regards Nationalist Taiwan as a renegade province and the
two are still technically at war. The Nationalists fled mainland
China to Taiwan in 1949 after the Communists defeated them in a
civil war.
</TEXT>
