<TEXT>
   Actor James Caan will undergo surgery
for a separated shoulder suffered when he crashed his motorcycle,
his publicist said.
   ``They are going to operate sometime this week and put a pin in
the shoulder,'' publicist Paul Bloch said Tuesday after visiting
Caan at St. Johns Hospital and Medical Center.
   ``He's still in a great amount of pain, but his spirits are
good,'' said Bloch.
   Four broken ribs were the only injuries originally reported after
Sunday's accident, but X-rays showed the 48-year-old actor injured
his shoulder.
