<HEAD>Doberman Wins Prestigious Westminster Dog Show ^Eds: SUBS 2nd, 3rd
grafs to CORRECT days; A vrsion moved on sports wires</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Doberman pinscher won Best in Show at the
Westminster Dog Show for the fourth time in the prestigious event's
113-year history.
   Champion Royal Tudor's Wild As the Wind, owned by Arthur and
Susan Korp and Beth Wilhite and Richard and Carolyn Vida, of San
Jose, Calif., won the honor Tuesday night in the show in which 2,628
dogs were entered.
