<FIRST>r a PM-DogRescue     02-15 0297</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Dog Rescue,0307</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dog Saves Owner During Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 108-pound dog whose owner was being
attacked by a robber crashed through a glass storm door and chased
the assailant away, police and the pet's owner said.
   ``I think the dog saved my life,'' said Buddy's owner, Peggy
Satterwhite.
   Mrs. Satterwhite said she was playing with Buddy, a Bernese
Mountain dog described as having the characteristics of a lamb, in
the back yard Tuesday morning when she heard the sound of breaking
glass. She went in to investigate.
   As soon as she walked in, a man grabbed her and began choking
her. ``I was gagging, couldn't breathe,'' she said.
   He demanded money, and while Mrs. Satterwhite struggled, he bound
and gagged her with duct tape. He took her wedding band, another
ring, her watch and two necklaces she was wearing.
   Outside, Buddy barked furiously. The robber cursed at the dog,
opened the storm door and threw a radio at him.
   The man beat Mrs. Satterwhite on the head and shoved her onto the
floor against a wall, she said. She only heard what happened next.
   ``Buddy crashed through that door like hell on fire,'' she said.
``Buddy chased the man.''
   As best as Mrs. Satterwhite can tell, the man raced through the
house and jumped out the same bedroom window he had broken to get
in. He escaped with the jewelry he had taken.
   After Mrs. Satterwhite worked her hands free, she found Buddy
sitting quietly in another room. He had suffered only a minor cut on
one paw. She telephoned her husband and police were summoned.
   Raleigh Police Officer D.A. Danielson investigated the attack.
``It's very true,'' he said. ``It's the dog that saved her.''
   Buddy dined on filet mignon Tuesday night.
</TEXT>
