<SECOND>PM-BRF--Last Legs,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>Peter Allen Show Posts Closing Notice</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Legs Diamond,'' the megabuck Peter Allen
musical that opened Dec. 26 to scathing reviews, will close Sunday,
the Broadway play's producers say.
   The play had $8 million in advance sales when it began previews
Oct. 18, and its investors had provided a $5 million bankroll. All
is lost, according to producer Arthur Rubin.
   Word-of-mouth about the play was negative from the beginning, and
the reviews found fault with every aspect of the show, a
fictionalized look at the Prohibition-era gangster.
   A dramatic increase in ticket sales could prolong the play's run,
a spokeswoman said, but chances of that happening are slim.
</TEXT>
