<SECOND>AM-BRF--Rhino Poachers,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Detained in Killing of Rhinoceros</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities have detained three people who
admitted that they killed a rhinoceros, an endangered species in
Nepal, and sold its horn for about $24,000.
   Conservation authorities still sought five other people allegedly
involved in the killing of the rhino in June in Royal Chitwan
National Park, 75 miles southwest of Katmandu, the news agency RSS
said Wednesday.
   The one-horned Asian rhinoceros is protected by Nepal law, and
its population has recovered to about 370, from 108 in 1967.
   Violators face up to three years in prison and fines of up to
$1,000.
