<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Flight103     02-15 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Flight 103,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Fined for Stealing Part of Flight 103 Wreckage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUMFRIES, Scotland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who admitted stealing a piece of
wreckage from the bombed Pan Am Flight 103 was fined about $265
Wednesday in Dumfries Sheriff's Court.
   Scott Thomson, 21, of nearby Ecclefechan, admitted taking a piece
of a landing gear disc, about 8 inches by 4 inches, from the main
highway past the town.
   The main part of the wreckage blasted a crater in Lockerbie after
the New York-bound plane exploded in flight on Dec. 21. All 259
people aboard the Boeing 747 were killed, as well as 11 residents of
the town.
   ``This was a mean and shameful offense,'' said Sheriff Kenneth
Barr, adding that if the theft had interfered with the
investigation, he would have imposed a long prison sentence.
   Three people are awaiting trial on similar charges.
</TEXT>
