<SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Dog,0086</SECOND>
<HEAD>Court Orders Car Seized Because Man Used It to Abandon Dog</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UDINE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge Wednesday ordered a man's car seized
to punish him for abandoning his dog on the roadside.
   Judge Giorgio Cabrini ruled the car of Ermanno Minghetti should
be seized because it was used to commit a crime. He was acting on a
complaint from an animal protection society.
   Minghetti, 49, denied the charge, saying he drove his dog out of
town because it needed exercise.
</TEXT>
