<HEAD>Clashes Close Schools in Zaire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KINSHASA, Zaire (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities closed the University of
Kinshasa and other schools in the capital Wednesday after two days
of clashes between police and students.
   The students have been protesting to demand a raise in their
monthly stipend of about $15. They also say they need more bus
service to get to classes.
   The official Zaire radio announced the closure and said the
schools would reopen March 1. It gave no other details.
   On Tuesday, students at the University of Kinshasa campus battled
police, and some officers were injured, witnesses said. About 20
people were arrested during the violence, which began Monday,
according to students who spoke on condition of anonymity.
