<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Brazil-Jews     02-15 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Brazil-Jews,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Anti-semitic Graffiti Painted on Brazilian Cathedral</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vandals spray-painted anti-Semitic
slogans Wednesday on the Metropolitan Cathedral, a landmark in this
inland capital.
   Graffiti reading ``The CNBB is Jewish'' and ``The Amazon is ours,
Jewish ecologists get out'' were painted on a wall outside the
cathedral, designed by the prominent Brazilian architect Oscar
Niemeyer and opened in 1967.
   A spokesman for the CNBB, the Portuguese acronym for the
Brazilian Roman Catholic Bishops' Conference, called the graffiti
``absurd and ridiculous.''
   The Rev. Felix Neefjes said the church has good relations with
the estimated 150,000 Jews in this predominantly Roman Catholic
country of 144 million people.
   The Bishops' Conference often has spoken out against destruction
of the Amazon rain forest and the invasion of Indian lands by miners
and wood cutters.
   ``One can understand an attack on the CNBB, but it makes no sense
to link Jews with it,'' Neefjes said.
</TEXT>
