<HEAD>Lawyer Fined $15,000 for Drunken Driving</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A lawyer has been fined $15,000 for drunken
driving, news reports said Wednesday.
   The penalty, which included a 21-day suspended jail sentence, was
levied Tuesday by an Oslo court under new rules pegging fines to
income. The unidentified 45-year-old lawyer earned about $190,000 a
year, newspapers said.
   The attorney was stopped in a random police check on a highway
north of Oslo, the reports said.
   The previous record fine was last month when a businessman found
guilty of drunken driving paid $11,200.
