<TEXT>
   Executive producer Bonny Dore said she got the
idea for the script for the upcoming HBO satire ``Glory, Glory!''
when she worked for Oral Roberts and found a similarity between
religion and variety shows.
   In the Feb. 18 issue of TV Guide, Ms. Dore said her work eight
years ago helped inspire the musical about an outspoken woman,
Sister Ruth, played by Ellen Greene, and an evangelist, played by
Richard Thomas.
   The producer said she was working on the ``Barbara Mandrell and
Mandrell Sisters Show'' eight years ago when Roberts asked her
advice. He wanted her to apply her glitzy, Hollywood-style expertise
to his prime-time TV shows.
   ``A lot of stuff in the script is right out of those days,'' Ms.
Dore said. ``I was struck by how similar religion and variety shows
were.''
