<HEAD>No Conflict in Bush Brother's Asia Business Trip, Fitzwater Says</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TERENCE HUNT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP White House Correspondent</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush's spokesman said Wednesday
there was nothing improper about Bush's brother, Prescott, trying to
drum up business in Asia for his consulting firm in advance of the
president's visit to the region next week.
   ``He's there as a private businessman,'' said White House
spokesman Marlin Fitzwater. ``No conflict in any way.''
   Calling the president's brother a ``very well respected
businessman,'' Fitzwater said Prescott Bush had received ``no
government help, government support, government contacts, government
aid in any way.''
