<HEAD>Jane Fonda and Tom Hayden Separate on Trial Basis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress and aerobics guru Jane Fonda and
husband Tom Hayden have decided to separate on a trial basis, a
spokesman for the couple said today.
   ``Tom and Jane consider this separation a private matter and will
have no public comment or statement on it,'' said Stephen Rivers.
   Fonda, 51, and Hayden, 49, a California assemblyman who first
rose to prominence as a co-founder of Students for a Democratic
Society and as a Chicago Seven defendant, were married in 1973.
   They have two children, Troy, 15, and Vanessa, who is Fonda's
daughter from a previous marriage to director Roger Vadim.
