<FIRST>r a PM-AvalancheDeaths     02-15 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Avalanche Deaths,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>2 Skiers Killed, 1 Hurt In Avalanche</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TELLURIDE, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two skiers were killed and a third was
injured when they were caught in an avalanche in an off-limits area
near Telluride ski area, authorities said today.
   The victims of the avalanche, which occurred Tuesday, were
identified as Anthony Shelly, 25, of Telluride, and Paul Wolfert,
whose age and hometown were not immediately available.
   A third skier, Todd Richards, 23, of Telluride, was in good
condition today at Montrose Memorial Hospital, hospital spokesman
Jerry Cooper said.
   San Miguel County Sheriff Bill Masters said the three were skiing
in a narrow passage in a back bowl outside the ski area when the
avalanche hit.
   The area had been roped off and clearly marked as off-limits to
skiers, and Masters said the men would have had to cross the ropes
to enter the area.
   Authorities learned of the avalanche after they were summoned to
the area by skiers in a nearby back bowl who heard Richards shouting
for help.
   Masters said sheriff's deputies used a specially trained dog to
find the victims.
</TEXT>
