<FIRST>r a AM-People-Powell     02-15 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Powell,0132</SECOND>
<HEAD>Retired Justice Discharged After Bout Of Pneumonia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Retired Supreme Court Justice Lewis F.
Powell Jr. is out of the hospital after eight days recovering from
pneumonia.
   Powell, 81, was given a week's supply of oral antibiotics and
told to rest before seeing his doctor again, Dr. Joel Schrank, an
attending physician, said Wednesday.
   Powell left Baptist Medical Center on Tuesday to return home to
the Washington area, said hospital spokesman Mark Glaser.
   He was admitted with an acute respiratory infection Feb. 6 after
complaining of dizziness while serving here on a federal appeals
court panel.
   The justice who spent 15 years on the Supreme Court before
retiring in 1987, citing health concerns as one reason. He had
suffered from prostate cancer.
</TEXT>
