<FIRST>r w AM-US-Jamaica     02-15 0090</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-US-Jamaica,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jamaica to Get More Hurricane Relief from U.S.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jamaica will receive $30 million in additional
U.S. assistance for hurricane relief, the Agency for International
Development announced Wednesday.
   The new aid is targeted for reconstruction of homes and public
buildings and restoration of water, electrical, health and
telecommunications services.
   Last September, Hurricane Gilbert wrecked tens of thousands of
homes and businesses and destroyed crops and power lines.
   The new aid package brings the total U.S. hurricane relief effort
in Jamaica to $154 million, AID said.
</TEXT>
