<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Sony     02-15 0228</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Sony,0236</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sony Earnings Rise 44.4 Percent In Latest Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sony Corp. said Wednesday its earnings rose 44.4
percent in its third fiscal quarter on the strength of healthy sales
gains.
   Half of the 36.8 percent increase in quarterly sales was the
result of Sony's $2 billion acquisition of CBS Records Inc., which
was announced in November 1987 and took effect in January 1988.
   By product area, Sony said sales rose 25 percent in video
equipment, 16 percent in audio equipment, 9 percent in televisions
and 22 percent in other products.
   Sony said its earnings for the period ended Dec. 31 totaled 28.9
billion yen, or $229 million, up from 20 billion yen a year earlier.
Sales totaled 613.8 billion yen, or $4.87 billion, up from 448.7
billion yen.
   For the first nine months of its fiscal year, Sony said its
earnings rose 107 percent to 58 billion yen, or $461 million, from
28 billion yen a year earlier. Sales rose 39.9 percent to 1,160
billion yen, or $12.7 billion, from 1,148 billion yen a year earlier.
   Results for 1987 were restated to reflect adoption of an
accounting standard that requires consolidation of its previously
unconsolidated subsidiaries. The dollar equivalents were calculated
on the basis of an exchange rate of 126 yen to the dollar that
prevailed at the end of the reporting period.
</TEXT>
