<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Limited     02-15 0220</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Limited,0228</SECOND>
<HEAD>Limited's Profit Up 90 Percent in Fourth Quarter</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: Tuesday is cq in 2nd graf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Limited Inc. said its fourth-quarter profit
soared 90 percent from a year earlier, boosted by a change in
merchandising strategy.
   The specialty apparel retailer reported Tuesday that its
fourth-quarter net income jumped to $120.1 million, or 67 cents a
share, from $63.3 million, or 35 cents a share, a year earlier.
   Fourth-quarter sales rose to $1.35 billion from $1 billion in the
year-earlier period.
   The performance in the quarter represents ``the results of
merchandising views that started to coalesce in May,'' said Ken
Gilman, Limited's executive vice president and chief financial
officer.
   ``We developed strong feelings about fall merchandise during the
back-to-school period, and those strong feelings enabled us to
position for a strong fourth quarter,'' he said.
   For the year, the retailer reported net income of $245.1 million,
or $1.36 a share, up from $235.2 million, or $1.25 a share, in 1987.
Annual sales rose to $4.07 billion from $3.5 billion the previous
year.
   The company operates 3,381 specialty apparel stores throughout
the United States under the names The Limited, Express, Henri
Bendel, Victoria's Secret, Lerner, Lane Bryant, Lerner Woman and
Abercrombie &amp; Fitch. It also distributes apparel nationally through
its Brylane and Victoria's Secret catalogue divisions.
</TEXT>
