<DATELINE>WARREN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A division of a Chrysler Corp. subsidiary
will supply axles to a Jeep-making factory in China for the next 10
years and provide technology which will allow the Chinese to build
their own axles, it was announced Wednesday.
   Thomas Stallkamp, chairman of Chrysler's Acustar Inc. parts
subsidiary, said the first 1,000 axles will be shipped in March to
Beijing Jeep Corp., which makes the Cherokee model of the
sport-utility vehicle. Shipment of up to 80,000 axles a year is
anticipated.
   Chrysler holds 31 percent equity in Beijing Jeep Corp.
