<SECOND>AM-Chrysler Audit,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chrysler Probing Alleged Fraud, Embezzlement, Report Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. has launched an
internal investigation into charges of fraud and embezzlement
involving middle-management executives, a Detroit television station
reported Wednesday.
   The probe is focusing on the automaker's Facilities Management
Department at company headquarters here, WXYZ-TV said.
   Chrysler confirmed Wednesday in a statement the existence of an
internal audit at the division. It said the investigation was
prompted by ``irregularities'' discovered by internal control
systems personnel.
   The company said the probe is routine and refused to elaborate.
   WXYZ reported that a top executive is being questioned along with
five others employees.
</TEXT>
